      <head>Iwan Knorr [pseud: I. O. Armand]</head>

      <div>
        <p>German composer and teacher.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <p>Knorr studied with Reinecke
          (composition), Moscheles (piano), and Jadassohn (theory) at the Leizpig Conservatory; from
          1874 he taught in Kharkiv, then from 1883 at the Hoch Conservatory, Frankfurt (piano,
          theory, history), where in 1908 he succeeded Bernhard Scholz as the Director. Among his
          pupils were Hans Pfitzner, Cyril Scott, Ernst Toch. and Reinhard Oppel.</p>
        
        <p>There is no correspondence, or indeed, so far as is known, personal contact, between
        Knorr and Schenker.</p>
      </div>
